Content: [dscrdvrsc] <fng77> I know we use AVX when mining in nhegminer, read a little about AVX at wikipedia. Then there is AVX2, Does that make any difference in hash rate? And question about AES, some cpu:s are have superfast MB/s in AES benchmarks, is that used by miner, the speed i mean? or is it just needed and the mining speed only depends on cores, ghz and cache?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdvrsc] <Cuttlebit> @fng77 You need SSE2 for "_mm_xor_si128", PCLMULQDQ for "_mm_clmulepi64_si128", SSSE3 for "_mm_mulhrs_epi16", AES-NI for "_mm_aesenc_si128 "

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdvrsc] <Cuttlebit> As far as I know you don't actually need AVX for mining Verus, but I read that nheqminer might need AVX to work on linux?
